    rem = p - tri[k]
    if rem==0:
        # nodes = k, unidirectional pairs = 0
        return (k, 0)
    # we will add one more SCC of size t where internal pairs = rem, but rem may not be triangular
    # we can take one extra node and form edges to make some mutual reachabilities:
    # minimal extra nodes: find minimal t such that tri[t] >= rem
    t = bisect.bisect_left(tri, rem)
    if tri[t]==rem:
        nodes = k + t
        # maximize unidirectional: make SCCs arranged in a chain so between SCCs edges are one-way
        # number of unidirectional pairs = sum over i<j sz[i]*sz[j]
        # with sizes: k and t => k*t
        return (nodes, k*t)
    else:
        # tri[t] > rem, so we need to create rem mutual pairs using one extra node connecting partly:
        # approach known from problem: you take k nodes forming one big SCC, then add one node connected both ways to some of existing nodes to add mutual pairs equal to rem by connecting to x nodes with two-way edges, but two-way with existing node yields mutual reachability pairs with that node.
